        "created_at": "2025-06-19T03:31:48.069Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello everyone,</p>\n<p>I’ve been trying to deploy the latest Signal Server (v20250409.1.0) on a VPS but haven’t had much luck. I followed several community tutorials and the official GitHub repo, but I keep running into configuration errors—especially around the service and secrets bundle YAML files. My main challenges are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Config complexity:</strong> The sample <code>server.yml</code> and <code>secrets-bundle.yml</code> from the repo include many options (payments, device checks, external services) that I don’t need, and I’m not sure which sections I can safely trim or stub out.</li>\n<li><strong>Budget constraints:</strong> I’m deploying on a single 4-core, 8 GB VPS and can’t afford paid managed services for DynamoDB, Redis clusters, Datadog, etc. I’d like to keep everything docker-based and self-hosted.</li>\n<li><strong>Outdated guides:</strong> Most blog posts I’ve found target older releases (3.x or pre-DynamoDB), and the layout of configs has changed significantly.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Could anyone point me to:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>A <strong>step-by-step, up-to-date</strong> guide (blog post, GitHub repo, or forum thread) for a <strong>minimal, private</strong> Signal Server deployment on Ubuntu 22.04 (or similar)?</li>\n<li>Tips on which config sections are <strong>mandatory</strong> versus which can be <strong>commented out</strong> for a basic messaging/presence-only setup?</li>\n<li>Examples of <code>.env</code>, <code>server.yml</code>, or <code>secrets-bundle.yml</code> that work with local Redis/DynamoDB-Local and stubbed-out external services?</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Any links, snippets, or advice you can share would be hugely appreciated. Thank you in advance!</p>\n<p>—</p>",
